    • Class org.cds06.speleograph.data.SpeleoDataFileReader.HeaderInformation extends Object implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      1L

      • Serialized Fields

        • numberOfSeriesToParse

          int numberOfSeriesToParse
          Number of read Series. This value is computed to go faster while iterating series or columns. It must be a computed value and never be visible for elements outside this class.

        • series

          Series[] series
          Series array, it contains all series to read mapped to an id (the index).

        • columns

          Integer[][] columns
          Columns array, contains the columns id to read for a Series.

          Each entry in this array is designed as the following rules :

          • [int]: is a single column data and series admit only a value per item
          • [int, int]: each item has a minimal value (first index) and maximal value(second index)
          • [int, int, int]: 0 is a value, 1 a minimal value and 2 a maximal value
          each entry in this array which has null length or length gather than 3 will be ignored.

        • firstLineOfData

          int firstLineOfData
          The line in the file where we will start to read data.

        • dateInformation

          SpeleoDataFileReader.DateInformation dateInformation
          Information about date columns.

          A column used for a Date element should not be used for a data.

        • columnSeparator

          char columnSeparator
          Separator for each column in this file.
